Thank you NBC 7 San Diego Joe Little.

post_text:
Last Monday, July 13th students, teachers, and staff in the Cajon Valley Union School District returned to their classrooms for in-person teaching and learning for the first time since schools were ordered to close in March. Every Elementary and Middle School is open in Cajon Valley. School principals reported that everyone, especially the students, were ecstatic to be back with their teachers and friends. It was also a chance to begin practicing the new safety protocols and guidelines for opening schools released by San Diego and California public health officials.

https://youtu.be/-TGsHUcHgDs

post_text:
We are aware that Cajon Valley Union School District employees recently posted offensive messages on social media regarding some of the activities taking place across our nation following the tragic death of George Floyd. I want our community to know that these postings, which appear to have been made outside of school hours, do not reflect the views or values of our school district. Our district is strongly committed to values of tolerance, compassion and respect. We are investigating the matter and will be taking appropriate corrective action if warranted. We will also be communicating with all staff to remind them about these values and their status as role models to children in our community.

David Miyashiro, Ed.D.
Superintendent

Students, parents, and teachers can explore nine different virtual career education sessions next week, while learning more about the people at the San Diego County Office of Education. ⁠
In collaboration with Cajon Valley Union School District, the SDCOE World of Work Week includes free, 30-minute online chats at 11 a.m. and 3 p.m. daily June 1 to 5. Each session includes time to meet a professional and ask them questions.⁠
The first one at 11 a.m. June 1 features San Diego County Superintendent of Schools Dr. Paul Gothold.
⁠Learn more at: https://sandiegocounty.nepris.com/home/v4
#distancelearning #remotelearning #worldofwork #careerpathways #CTEinCA

While life as we know it continues its slow re-opening, let's face it, things are still weird and will take some adjustment. But your Panda fix doesn't have change!

It's another Panda Express fundraiser for Hillsdale Music on WEDNESDAY, MAY 27, ALL DAY.

Don't worry about your meal prep--go to Panda Express in Rancho San Diego! Your family will love it, you won't have to cook, and the Hillsdale Music Department will get a portion of the proceeds (we need this now more than ever!).

Just show this flyer on your phone when checking out and mention you're here for the fundraiser. Or order online and enter 310144 in the promo code box.

Thank you!

"Save a Musician. Eat a Panda."

Hillsdale Middle School Huskies

text:
Hillsdale Music Department Parent Association - HMDPA
May 24 at 6:06 PM ·

While life as we know it continues its slow re-opening, let's face it, things are still weird and will take some adjustment. But your Panda fix doesn't have change!

It's another Panda Express fundraiser for Hillsdale Music on WEDNESDAY, MAY 27, ALL DAY.

Don't worry about your meal prep--go to Panda Express in Rancho San Diego! Your family will love it, you won't have to cook, and the Hillsdale Music Department will get a portion of the proceeds (we need this now more than ever!).

Just show this flyer on your phone when checking out and mention you're here for the fundraiser. Or order online and enter 310144 in the promo code box.

Thank you!

"Save a Musician. Eat a Panda."

Hillsdale Middle School Huskies
Hillsdale Middle PTA
Cajon Valley Union School District

TEDxKids@ElCajon team has decided to make this year's event virtual through Zoom! We look forward to bringing our community back together through the amazing ideas from our selected 2020 TEDxKids@ElCajon speakers! Join us June 3rd-5th, as we #StayHome and imagine "My Future Possible Self"

Registration for the virtual event will be available on www.tedxkidselcajon.com shortly

Magnolia Elementary School
May 8 at 4:14 PM ·

Weekly Update!

We have completed week 3 of distance learning. We hope you are settling in to some routines and doing well. If you need anything, please let us know. You can message us here, contact the office, or send us an email.

*Email is one of our primary ways to communicate with families.

Check your email for some fun teacher appreciation events.

We also sent a survey via email to get your input on how things are going for your family during school closure.

Not getting our emails? Call the front office @ 619-588-3080 and we will add you email to your student's profile.

Happy #TeacherAppreciationWeek! The best teachers make students' social and emotional health a priority and challenge their students to stay focused, work hard, and believe in themselves. CholeAnne Dilgard (Fuerte Falcons PTA, Cajon Valley Union School District), Alexis Downey Beadle (Salt Creek Elementary, Chula Vista Elementary School District), Robyn Elsmore (Enrique S. Camarena Elementary, Chula Vista Elementary School District), Deirdre Fabian (Samuel F. B. Morse High School, San Diego Unified School District), Erin Ferguson (Mission Estancia Elementary, Encinitas Union School District), Suzanne Fermia (Ditmar Elementary School, Oceanside Unified School District), Jasmie Feser (Steam Academy at La Presa, La Mesa-Spring Valley Schools), Kimberly Gardner (Mike Choate Center, Fallbrook Union Elementary School District), and Angela Gigliotti Ortiz (Bayside Community School, SDCOE) are examples of this in action. Check out our YouTube playlist to meet these inspirational educators! https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLl574UpZ180JI8bKehZOZTipdDagfRVH4

shared_text:
Tita Cordero-Bautista
May 4 at 1:21 PM ·

Today is May the 4th. If we were at school, we would all have our favorite Star Wars gear on. Here’s a picture of my friends and I while we were running the Star Wars challenge. We stopped and waited almost 30 minutes in line to take a picture with Chewbacca right in the middle of our race. It took a long time, but you can tell from our smiles, we were so happy to get a photo.

I’ve been waiting a long time to see all of the students, staff members and families of Vista Grande. I can only imagine that when that day comes, that smiles will be accompanied with tears of joy. Be safe, and stay apart, so we can be together again.
Vista Grande Elementary Vista Grande PTA Cajon Valley Union School District

post_text:
Our goal at Cajon Valley is to support you and your child in learning together, which will mean calling on our collective knowledge, creativity, patience, and flexibility.

As we begin a distance learning program, our first goal as educators is to reestablish relationships and connect with your children utilizing online support and strategies. This will present new challenges, but Cajon Valley staff and students are prepared to overcome them. We have been implementing a 1:1 blended learning model since 2014 and our students and staff are accustomed to using technology for learning. We look forward to working collaboratively with you to make the most out of this difficult situation. David Miyashiro California Department of Education U.S. Department of Education San Diego County Office of Education El Cajon, California Association of California School Administrators #covid19 #distancelearning #distanceeducation #elementaryschool #pivot

https://youtu.be/S-8GmWbW7yM

text:
Our goal at Cajon Valley is to support you and your child in learning together, which will mean calling on our collective knowledge, creativity, patience, and flexibility.

As we begin a distance learning program, our first goal as educators is to reestablish relationships and connect with your children utilizing online support and strategies. This will present new challenges, but Cajon Valley staff and students are prepared to overcome them. We have been implementing a 1:1 blended learning model since 2014 and our students and staff are accustomed to using technology for learning. We look forward to working collaboratively with you to make the most out of this difficult situation. David Miyashiro California Department of Education U.S. Department of Education San Diego County Office of Education El Cajon, California Association of California School Administrators #covid19 #distancelearning #distanceeducation #elementaryschool #pivot

https://youtu.be/S-8GmWbW7yM

YOUTUBE.COM
Cajon Valley Distance Learning

FOR OUR 5TH GRADE FAMILIES FROM HILLSDALE:

Hello Future Hillsdale Families,

I hope everyone is doing well during this unprecedented time. We are beginning to work on our schedule for the 2020/2021 school year. A key piece to building the schedule is understanding the electives that our students want to take. We are asking that future Hillsdale students complete a Google Form to help us place students correctly for the 2020/2021 school year. You child will be receiving the survey from their current teacher. Please look to their Google Classroom and/or the 5th grade playlist for the survey. Thank you for your time and stay safe.

Jake Launder
Hillsdale Middle School Principal

Good evening Anza families!

We are kicking off our new Distance Learning on Monday, April 20. Teachers will be sending out an ePlaylist each Monday by 9:00 a.m. which will provide lessons and activities to complete throughout the week. Teachers will be communicating with students and families via Zoom and other platforms and hold office hours each week to provide instructional support and connect with students. Please look for more information to come from your child's teacher.

As we begin our new Distance Learning program, we ask for your continued participation, cooperation and support. Have a wonderful weekend.
